        "answer_count": 5,
        "title": "Printing something in Java after a certain amount of time has passed",
        "body": "<p>I'm working on a text adventure game for my Java class, and I'm running into a problem while trying to time a print statement from showing up in the console.<\/p>\n\n<p>Basically after 45 seconds I would like a print statement to show up, in this case the print statement would be reminding the user that they need to let their virtual dog out...<\/p>\n\n<p>I also need the timer to reset after the user gives the correct command.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 18478677,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "timer"
        ],
        "score": 4,
        "accepted_answer_id": 18478710,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 14583,
        "last_edit_date": 1516825352
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/291a71a3d9ae5305f07ab42ad15745e6?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2983071,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2532621,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2532621/ash",
                "reputation": 5175,
                "display_name": "ash"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 8,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1554401960,
            "creation_date": 1377659041,
            "body": "<pre><code>import java.util.Timer;\nimport java.util.TimerTask;\n\n...\n\nTimer timer = new Timer();\ntimer.schedule(new TimerTask() { \n   @Override  \n   public void run() {\n       System.out.println(\"delayed hello world\");\n   }\n},  45000);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/index.html?java/util/Timer.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Timer<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/index.html?java/util/TimerTask.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">TimerTask<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>To cancel the timer, either use a TimerTask variable to remember the task and then call its cancel() method, or use <code>timer.purge()<\/code>; the latter cancels all tasks on the timer.  To schedule the task again, just repeat.<\/p>\n\n<p>You'll probably want to do more advanced operations in the future, so reading the Timer API docs is a good idea.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 18478710,
            "question_id": 18478677,
            "last_edit_date": 1554401960
        },
        {
